# Voice hotkeys (Windows quickstart)

This repo includes `scripts/voice_hotkeys.py`, which lets you trigger keyboard hotkeys using openWakeWord.

## What it does (recommended pair)

- Say **"hey jarvis"** → holds **Ctrl + Alt**
- Say **"alexa"** → releases **Ctrl + Alt**

## Setup (recommended: virtualenv)

From the repo root (`C:\Users\caleb\Documents\Coding\openWakeWord`):

```powershell
python -m venv .venv
.\.venv\Scripts\python -m pip install -U pip

# install openWakeWord (editable) + its runtime deps
.\.venv\Scripts\python -m pip install -e .

# microphone capture + keyboard control
.\.venv\Scripts\python -m pip install sounddevice pynput
```

## One-time model download

```powershell
.\.venv\Scripts\python -c "import openwakeword; openwakeword.utils.download_models()"
```

## Run

```powershell
.\.venv\Scripts\python scripts\voice_hotkeys.py --whisper-model "hey jarvis" --hush-model "alexa"
```

## Tips

- If your microphone won’t open at 16kHz, set the Windows device “Default format” to **16000 Hz**.
- To list audio devices:

```powershell
.\.venv\Scripts\python scripts\voice_hotkeys.py --list-devices
```

